# Design system rules (tokens first)

Aligns with [Code-Jedi.md](../docs/Code-Jedi.md) §5 (Global Shield), [studio-dark-ui.mdc](./studio-dark-ui.mdc), and skill [studio-dark-shield.md](../skills/studio-dark-shield.md). Path B consumers also follow [tailwind-shadcn-bridge.mdc](./tailwind-shadcn-bridge.mdc).

## Tokens first (mandatory)

1. **All color and spacing values** used in components must exist as `--msc-*` variables in `ui/msc-shield.css` before use anywhere else.
2. If a new color is required, **add the variable to the Shield** — not to a satellite file, not to `tailwind.config.ts`, not inline in TSX.
3. Satellites (`ui/msc-[feature].css`) reference only `var(--msc-*)` and optional **wrapper modifier** variables (e.g. `--msc-portfolio-media-height` on `.msc-portfolio-wrapper`).

## Component architecture

- **Design system first:** Use existing `ui/msc-*.tsx` primitives and `.msc-card-panel` patterns before creating new markup.
- **Namespace wrappers:** Every feature block uses a unique container (`.msc-portfolio-wrapper`, `.msc-dashboard-wrapper`, `.msc-auth-wrapper`).
- **No bare-tag styling:** Do not target global `div`, `p`, `button`, or `body` selectors outside Shield scope.
- **Props:** TypeScript interfaces for component props; extend via `className` + satellite CSS, not ad-hoc `style` for theme values.

## What to avoid

- Hardcoded hex/rgb/hsl in TSX, CSS satellites, or Tailwind arbitrary values when a token exists.
- Duplicating token names (`--background` vs `--msc-bg-main`) without documenting the bridge in `tailwind-shadcn-bridge.mdc`.
- Monolithic CSS files — one feature → one `ui/msc-[feature].css` satellite.

## Agent checklist

- [ ] Checked `ui/msc-shield.css` for existing variable
- [ ] New styles in scoped satellite or shadcn component file
- [ ] Wrapper class present on feature root
- [ ] No contradictions with `studio-dark-ui.mdc` or `tailwind-shadcn-bridge.mdc`
